content: I go back to the lines as far as I am able to.

I don't discard the old interpretations completely. But I keep an open mind of which metaphor is operating in the moment, which I believe is more traditional when reading the Yijing. There are plenty of metaphors between the lines; active/passive, man/woman, gentleman/villain, ruler/subject etc but some books or writers are quite strict about which hexagram meaning what. And when I say I discard certain readings, I only mean that I don't stick to them as strictly as the writer did, or as some new Yijing users do.
